Alexthe668
@everyone @deleted-role Meet the 80th mob for Alex's Mobs, and the fifth and final mob for the Wilder Update, the Sugar Glider! This tiny marsupial spawns exclusively within the birch forest biome, and can be seen gliding between the logs and branches of these trees. Sugar Gliders use their long membranes between their limbs to do so. Due to their fondness for fruit & sweets, they can be tamed with sweet berries. Tamed Sugar gliders will not attack, but can be sneak+clicked onto their owners head. Occasionally, tamed sugar gliders will search through leaves blocks for items - which can vary from sticks to saplings, to even rare forest-related items like Hair of Bear and Moose Antlers, that have been lost in the foliage.
